This article is an executive order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. The order establishes the White House Office of Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships, which will be responsible for coordinating the federal government's efforts to work with faith-based and secular organizations to address the needs of underserved communities. The office will assist in organizing effective service efforts, develop policies affecting community programs, ensure consistency with constitutional commitments, and promote partnerships between civil society and the government. The order also amends previous executive orders related to faith-based and community initiatives and revokes a previous executive order establishing the White House Faith and Opportunity Initiative. The implementation of this order will be subject to applicable law and available appropriations.